args:
The whole town is in a Valentine's mood,
and ready to reveal their deepest feelings.
Naturally, Orion is equally excited for this
auspicious occasion.
Ah, Valentine's! You are truly the most\nexciting time of the year!
The ladies who walk the streets shine\nmore radiantly than ever—and so shall I!
I've even prepared a new outfit just for\nthe occasion—all I need now is a partner.\n...Excuse me! Young lady!
Ah, your beauty increased the moment you\nturned to face me. I think I'm in love!
What say you to joining me for\na cup of tea, fair maiden?
What say you to a knuckle sandwich?!
I got no interest in guys what got nothin'\nbetween the ears! Now scram before\nI wipe the floor with yer face!
Goodness, but she was aggressive!\nAh well. Can't expect to win them all,\nright?
But soft! Another beautiful damsel walks\nthe streets! ...Excuse me, fair lady?
Ah, what a lovely voice you have.\nMy heart threatens to tear itself\nfrom my very chest at your tremolo!
Might you do me the honor of\naccompanying me on a date?
Wh-what? You don't even know me!\nAre you a crazy person or something?\nHalp! Haaaaaalp!
Oh my. That...could have gone better?
I seem to be off my game today;\nI'm receiving naught but rejection!
But it's too early to be giving up!\nI simply need to keep searching\nfor more fateful encounters.
Hello, Orion. Er, what's wrong?\nYou look really pale.
My dear friend, you must help me.\nMy very life itself is in danger!
No matter how many women I invite\non dates, not a single one accepts!
Are ya daft? 'Course yer gonna get\nsome rejection if ya ask out every\nsingle person ya see!
But I was rejected by ALL of them!\nEvery one, to a man! ...Er, woman.\nIs such a thing even possible?
I do not accept this! There is simply no\nconceivable way I could be turned down\nby that many women in a row.
There's mischief afoot. Mischief, I say!\nI've never seen such a run of foul luck!
Everyone else is getting more and more\ninto the spirit of Valentine's, and yet\npoor Orion sits rejected and alone.
I think I understand the problem.\nMight I have a moment, Orion?
I think the issue lies in how you are\napproaching all of these women.
They don't think you are serious.
I've spent time with you here in the castle,\nso I know that deep down—VERY deep,\nmind you—you are actually quite sincere.
But if you suddenly call out to people on\nthe streets who don't know your nature,\nthey're naturally going to be suspicious.
Alas! Alas and alack! Oh, but this is\nMOST vexing, Cleo. What should I do?!
How about givin' the whole date thing\na rest for a little bit, champ?
I couldn't possibly! How would I LIVE?!
There must be SOMETHING I can do to\nmake the world stop spinning widdershins\nupon its axis of love!
I can see you're serious about this.
I have never been more so.
Your Highness, you can't possibly be\nthinking of HELPING this cad!
I can't ignore a friend in need.
So if he truly needs my help,\nI'm going to give it.
If someone is going to do this,\nit should be me.
What this man needs is to learn more\nabout what women think—which means\nhe needs to learn that FROM a woman.
Is this acceptable to you, Orion?
Naturally! I would never pass up an\nopportunity to learn from a member\nof the fairer sex!
Well then, here's lesson one:\nDON'T USE THE TERM ＂FAIRER SEX＂!
Cleo, this is madness—but if you insist\non doing it, you must permit me to help.
I hope something good comes of this.
But I have to admit, I'm worried...
